The Nelspruit Police Station will be temporarily closed after a police official tested positive for Covid-19. Brig Leonard Hlathi, the provincial police spokesperson,  said, “The Community Service Centre will now be operated from a caravan which is set up at the front entrance of the police station which is at 15 Bester Street.” ALSO READ:Top politician arrested for alleged rape Mbombelans who need to be assisted are requested to call  072- 859- 0038, for any emergencies and complaints which will be attended to. “The telephone lines at Nelspruit Police Station Community Service Centre will not be accessible for the duration of the closure. However, service delivery will not be hampered,” said Hlathi. ALSO READ: Mpumalanga police recover suspected stolen copper cables worth an estimated R700 000 He added that the building will be decontaminated and services are expected to continue as normal on Thursday. “The SAPS management in Mpumalanga apologises for any inconvenience that may arise from this. The station commander, Maj Gen Dorah Xaba, can  be contacted on 082-970-5761 or the Visible Policing commander, Col Bheki Mlambo, who can be reached  on 082- 462- 2582,” he concluded